To generate a random number between a range of two given number 
                                                    --> function randomTime(min,max){
                                                            return Math.round(Math.random()*(max-min)+min);
                                                          } 

The globally declared values may vary while reinitialisations, only gets its predefined value on the page reload;

let timeUp = false; (value assigned on global scope);
couple functions redeclare its value to true when the chances meet;

function startGame(){
  scoreBoard.textContent = 0;
  timeUp = false;
  score = 0;
  peep();
  setTimeout(()=>timeUp = true,10000);
}

to run the above function,
the variable timeUp needed to be reassigned;
